  "prompt": "What is the most underrated romantic movie?",
  "response": "Opinions on what constitutes the \"most underrated\" romantic movie can vary widely depending on personal taste and cultural context. However, one film that is often mentioned in discussions about underrated romantic movies is \"Before Sunrise\" (1995), directed by Richard Linklater. This film features Ethan Hawke and Julie Delpy as two strangers who meet on a train and spend a night together in Vienna, sharing deep conversations and forming a profound connection.\n\nDespite its critical acclaim, \"Before Sunrise\" did not achieve massive commercial success upon its initial release, but it has since gained a dedicated following and is highly regarded for its natural dialogue, chemistry between the leads, and exploration of love and human connection.\n\nOther films that are sometimes considered underrated include \"Once\" (2007), \"Her\" (2013), and \"Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind\" (2004). Each of these films brings a unique perspective to the genre and has garnered a loyal fanbase over the years.",
